### 1. Register User
POST http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/v1/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Test User",
  "email": "test@example.com",
  "password": "password123",
  "password_confirmation": "password123"
}

###

### 2. Login
POST http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/v1/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "test@example.com",
  "password": "password123"
}

###

### 3. Upload PDF (Replace TOKEN with actual token from login)
# Use Postman/Insomnia for file upload, or curl:
# curl -X POST http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/v1/pdf/upload \
#   -H "Authorization: Bearer YOUR_TOKEN" \
#   -F "pdf=@path/to/file.pdf"

POST http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/v1/pdf/upload
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_TOKEN_HERE
Content-Type: multipart/form-data

# Add PDF file here using Postman/Insomnia

###

### 4. Chat Query - WebSocket (Replace TOKEN and pdf_id)
POST http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/v1/chat/query
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_TOKEN_HERE
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "query": "What is this document about?",
  "pdf_id": 3
}

###

### 4b. Chat Query - Synchronous (Get answer directly)
POST http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/v1/chat/query-sync
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_TOKEN_HERE
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "query": "What is this document about?",
  "pdf_id": 3
}

